  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NIVA Plastic and Chemical Pollution</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective is to build knowledge and capacity to tackle plastic and chemical pollution from important sources in India. The project will support India&apos;s ambitious targets to reduce plastic releases and enhance its efforts to implement the Stockholm Convention on persistent organic pollutants. Two case study areas are selected - Ganges river catchment and the Gujarat state. NIVA will partner with Indian institutions.</narrative>
  </description>
